Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice (see pantry for amount) into a #medium saucepan{} with a #tight-fitting lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the #lid{}.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{260%g} and sliced pepper and fry, stirring, until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @Diced Chorizo{90%g} to the pan and fry until the chicken is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked through when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Cut the @Lemon{1} into wedges.

Once the chorizo is browned, reduce the heat to medium-high, then add the garlic, @Tomato Puree{30%g} and @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Fry, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Honey{1%tbsp} and @Water{100%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts) into the #frying pan{}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once the rice is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{} and gently stir it into the spicy sauce.

Stir through the @Peas{120%g}, @Sun-Dried Tomato Paste{25%g} and a good squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and add more salt and pepper or lemon juice if needed.

Share the spiced chicken and chorizo rice between your #bowls{}.

Serve with any remaining lemon wedges.

Enjoy!